            <p>Verner's Law also affects several common Class II verbs such as '<em>freosan - to freeze</em>',
                '<em>dreosan - to fall</em>', '<em>leosan - to lose</em>', and '<em>seoðan - to boil</em>',
                with the '<strong>s</strong>' becoming '<strong>r</strong>' and the '<strong>ð</strong>'
                becoming '<strong>d</strong>'. So '<em>hie freosaþ - they freeze</em>' becomes
                '<em>hie fruron - they froze</em>', and
                '<em>hie seoþaþ - they boil</em>' becomes '<em>hie sudon - they boiled</em>'.
            </p>
